body:
Hi,

I ran today into an issue with event bubbling from child components to parents. The problem is as follows: I have child component which handles a form and attaches itself to the onSubmit event. On form submit the Child handler does its stuff and doesn't return false so the event bubbles. The Parent component attaches one onSubmit handler to the child but this handler doesn't get called. The funny thing is that if attach a onSubmit handler on an element which wraps the Child this handlers does get called.

Below is some sample code ([fiddle available](http://jsfiddle.net/kk65fa3k/))

``` js
var Parent = React.createClass({

    handleDivSubmit: function(){
        alert('Handle Div Submit'); // This gets called
        return false;
    },

    handleChildSubmit: function(){
        alert('Handle Child submit'); // This doesn't get called
        return false;
    },

    render: function() {
        return <div onSubmit={this.handleDivSubmit}>
            <Child onSubmit={this.handleChildSubmit}/>
        </div>;
    }
});

var Child = React.createClass({

    handleSubmit: function(){
        alert('Submit on child'); // This gets called
    },

    render: function(){
        return (
            <form onSubmit={this.handleSubmit}>
                <input type='submit'/>
            </form>
            );
    }
});

React.renderComponent(<Parent name="World" />, document.body);
```

Don't know if this is the expected behaviour or a bug because I didn't found anything related to this on the documentation or as a previous issue.
